## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="4bccc-102">Utilizzare un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.StopStoryboard> azione con un <xref:System.Windows.EventTrigger> o <xref:System.Windows.Trigger> per interrompere in modo interattivo un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4bccc-102">Use a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.StopStoryboard> action with an <xref:System.Windows.EventTrigger> or <xref:System.Windows.Trigger> to interactively stop a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="4bccc-103"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.StopStoryboard> interessa solo un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> quando è attivo (dopo il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> Avvia).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4bccc-103"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.StopStoryboard> only affects a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> when it is active (after the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> starts).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4bccc-104">L'arresto di uno storyboard di <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.CurrentGlobalSpeedInvalidated> e <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.CurrentStateInvalidated> eventi, ma non il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Completed> evento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4bccc-104">Stopping a storyboard triggers the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.CurrentGlobalSpeedInvalidated> and <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.CurrentStateInvalidated> events, but not the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Completed> event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="4bccc-105"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> non fa riferimento a un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> direttamente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4bccc-105"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> does not reference a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> directly.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4bccc-106">Piuttosto, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> deve fare riferimento il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> del <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> che controlla il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4bccc-106">Rather, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> must reference the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> that controls the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4bccc-107">Vedere [procedura: utilizzare i trigger di evento per controllare un Storyboard dopo l'avvio](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) per un esempio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4bccc-107">See [How to: Use Event Triggers to Control a Storyboard After It Starts](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) for an example.</span></span>  
  
